This paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze self-reported behavior on Twitter, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses semantic clustering and distributional semantics techniques, which are commonly used in information retrieval and machine learning (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper analyzes large text corpora, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.SD). The paper also uses statistical methods to analyze the data, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to map text corpora to a dimensional model of affect, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
